# Customer Discovery Summary

## Project Title

Lost & Found System

## Target Users Studied

* University Students
* University Staff

## Number of Responses / Interviews

15 Survey Responses

## Main Repeated Problem

Many students lose personal items on campus and find it difficult to get them back.

## Main Current Workarounds

* Asking friends
* Posting on social media
* Checking with security or campus offices

## Strongest Evidence Found

Most respondents said they have lost or found items on campus. Many also said they would use a Lost & Found website if it was available.

## Weak Evidence or Unclear Findings

Some respondents said they rarely lose items, so they may not use the system often.

## What We Must Revise

We need to make the system simple and easy to use for students and staff.

## Decision for Next Lab

* Continue with same problem direction

## Updated Problem Statement

University students and staff need an easy way to report and find lost items because current methods are slow and not organized.

